    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <head>10. National Security Decision Memorandum 1<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d10fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–208, National Security
                        Decision Memoranda, <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 1.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-01-20">January 20, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Vice President</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of State </item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense </item>
                    <item>The Secretary of the Treasury </item>
                    <item>The Administrator of the Agency for International Development </item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence </item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff </item>
                    <item>The Director of the US Information Agency </item>
                    <item>The Director of the Office of Emergency Preparedness </item>
                    <item>The Director of the Bureau of the Budget</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Establishment of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Decision and Study
                        Memoranda Series</item>
                </list>
                <p>At the direction of the President, the following two memoranda series are hereby
                    established to inform the Departments and Agencies of Presidential action: <list>
                        <item>—<hi rend="italic">National Security Decision Memoranda (<gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss>).</hi> This series shall be used
                            to report Presidential decisions (whether the result of <gloss
                                target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                            <pb facs="0061" n="30" xml:id="pg_30"/> meetings or appropriate
                            consultation with the Department head concerned).<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d10fn2">Copies of <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 1
                                through <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 264 (August 6, 1974)
                                are ibid., Boxes H–208– H–248. Copies of <gloss target="#t_NSDM1"
                                    >NSDM</gloss> 1 through <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss>
                                348 (January 20, 1977) are ibid., <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss>
                                59, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>– <gloss target="#t_NSDM1"
                                    >NSDM</gloss> Files: Lot 83D305.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item>—<hi rend="italic">National Security Study Memoranda (<gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss>).</hi> This series shall be used
                            to direct that studies be undertaken (normally for <gloss
                                target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> consideration).<note n="3"
                                xml:id="d10fn3">Copies of <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 1
                                through <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 206 (July 29, 1974)
                                are in the National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 365, Subject Files,
                                National Security Study Memoranda. Copies of <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 1 through <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 248 (November 13, 1976) and
                                follow-up studies, organized by <gloss target="#t_NSSM1"
                                    >NSSM</gloss> number, are in ibid., <gloss target="#t_RG1"
                                    >RG</gloss> 59, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> Files: Lot 83D212, and copies of
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 1 through <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 200 are also in ibid., Nixon
                                Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files,
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files
                                (H-Files), Boxes H–122-H–207, National Security Study
                                Memoranda.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The National Security Action Memoranda (<gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>)
                    series is hereby abolished. An <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> to be
                    issued shortly will describe the status of existing <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                        >NSAM</gloss>s.<note n="4" xml:id="d10fn4">In <gloss target="#t_NSDM1"
                            >NSDM</gloss> 5, February 3, the President listed 30 <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s that would continue in force until
                        further notice, specified a review process for 40 other <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s, and directed that all other <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s “be considered inactive as of this
                        date.” (Ibid., Box H–209)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Henry A. Kissinger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
